  <title>Troubleshooting</title>
  <section>
    <title>403 Forbidden</title>
    <para>
      The server is responding with HTTP 403 Forbidden
    </para>
    <para>
      The request was valid, but the server is refusing action.
      The user might not have the necessary permissions for a resource, or may need an account of some sort.
    </para>
    <para>
      A potential issue can be a wrong <emphasis>Accept</emphasis> and/or <emphasis>Content-Type</emphasis>  
    </para>
    <important>
      <para>
        Both request haeder have to be <emphasis role="stromg">application/scim+json</emphasis>.
      </para>
      <para>
        Neither <emphasis role="stromg">application/json</emphasis> or <emphasis role="stromg">application/json+scim</emphasis> are valid values for the request headers.
      </para>
    </important>
  </section>
</chapter>